---
import EnLayout from '../../layouts/EnLayout.astro';
const seo = `<meta name="robots" content="index, follow, max-image-preview:large">
<title>About BlogKub | Free no-code Blogger theme builder</title>
<meta name="description" content="BlogKub is a free, 100% client-side tool for building and customizing Blogger themes with no coding. Read on to learn where it came from, what we believe, and who we build it for.">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://www.blogkub.com/en/about">
<meta property="og:type" content="website">
<meta property="og:site_name" content="BlogKub">
<meta property="og:title" content="About BlogKub | Free Blogger theme builder">
<meta property="og:description" content="Where BlogKub came from, what we believe, and who we build it for.">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://www.blogkub.com/en/about">
<meta property="og:image" content="https://www.blogkub.com/android-chrome-512x512.png">
<meta property="og:locale" content="en_US">
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[
{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#organization","name":"BlogKub","url":"https://www.blogkub.com/","description":"A no-code tool for building and customizing Blogger themes, running 100% in the browser","founder":{"@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#patpisan"}},
{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#patpisan","name":"Patpisan Dathong","alternateName":["PATPISAN DATHONG","Ben","LuMoo"],"url":"https://www.blogkub.com/en/about","image":"https://www.blogkub.com/author-patpisan.png","jobTitle":"Founder and author of BlogKub","worksFor":{"@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#organization"},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/patpisan","https://pantip.com/profile/2448725"]},
{"@type":"AboutPage","@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/en/about#webpage","url":"https://www.blogkub.com/en/about","name":"About BlogKub","inLanguage":"en","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#website"},"about":{"@id":"https://www.blogkub.com/#organization"}},
{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[
{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.blogkub.com/en/"},
{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"About"}]}
]}</script>`;
const body = `<main class="wrap"><article class="doc">
<nav class="crumb"><a href="/en/">Home</a> › <span>About</span></nav>
<span class="pill">About us</span>
<h1>Build a Blogger theme <span class="g">anyone can make</span>, with no code</h1>
<p class="lead">BlogKub is a tool for building and customizing themes for Blogger that runs entirely in your browser. It is free, needs no account, and needs no coding background. We want every blogger, from complete beginner to seasoned pro, to have a site that looks good, loads fast, and does SEO properly, without wrestling with complex XML files or hiring a developer.</p>

<h2>What BlogKub is</h2>
<p>Blogger is a powerful, free blogging platform, but making a theme look good and get SEO right usually means editing complicated XML, which is a wall for most people. <strong>BlogKub exists to take that wall down.</strong> You assemble a page from drag-and-drop "blocks", adjust text, colors, and fonts, turn features on or off, then download a ready-to-use Blogger XML file that you upload straight to your blog.</p>

<h2>What we believe</h2>
<div class="grid">
  <div class="card"><strong>Free and accessible</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">A good tool should not be walled off by price. Everyone deserves to build a beautiful site.</p></div>
  <div class="card"><strong>Privacy first</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">100% client-side. Your project data stays in your browser and is never sent to a server.</p></div>
  <div class="card"><strong>Professional quality</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">Every theme ships with sound SEO structure, schema, and speed right out of the box.</p></div>
</div>

<h2>How it works</h2>
<p>Everything happens in your own browser, with nothing uploaded to a server. It takes just a few steps.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Pick a template</strong> that matches your kind of site, and the essential blocks and features are set up for you automatically.</li>
  <li><strong>Customize</strong> the text, images, colors, and fonts, and reorder blocks by dragging them.</li>
  <li><strong>Download the XML</strong> and upload it to Blogger through Theme → Backup/Restore.</li>
</ul>
<p>Want to see how each feature works? Read the detailed guides in the <a href="/en/learn/">BlogKub Learning Center</a>, with a walkthrough and screenshots for every feature.</p>

<h2>Customize every part of your menu, without touching code</h2>
<p>The menu is the heart of how people move around your site, but on Blogger, making one that looks good and works well usually means editing XML by hand. <strong>BlogKub turns that into a matter of clicking and typing.</strong> You can add, remove, rename, and reorder menu items yourself, just by dragging and typing, with no need to know a single line of code, and everything is turned into a ready-to-use theme automatically.</p>
<p>Just as important, menus are designed to <strong>look good and work well on every screen size.</strong> The layout adapts to each reader's device automatically, on both desktop and mobile.</p>
<div class="grid">
  <div class="card"><strong>🖥️ Desktop menu</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">A full-width horizontal bar, with menu items on the left or right, balancing your logo, links, and buttons cleanly.</p></div>
  <div class="card"><strong>📱 Mobile menu</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">Collapses to a hamburger button with a panel that slides in from either side, easy to tap and never covering your content.</p></div>
  <div class="card"><strong>⬇️ Automatic bottom bar on mobile</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">A bottom navigation bar appears on its own for phones, so readers reach your key links with a natural thumb tap.</p></div>
  <div class="card"><strong>🗂️ Submenu support</strong><p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15px;margin:.4em 0 0">Build dropdown submenus to group content into layers, keeping a site with many categories tidy.</p></div>
</div>
<p>You set all of this in one place inside the Builder, and BlogKub handles how it renders on each device. You get a menu that looks good, matches your theme, and works from the very first time, without spending any effort on code.</p>

<h2>Who BlogKub is for</h2>
<p>From beginners taking their first steps to people who want a Blogger site that looks professional and does real SEO, without hiring a developer. Whether it is a personal blog, a travel blog, product reviews, an online course, or a company site, BlogKub has templates and features ready for you.</p>

<h2>Our mission</h2>
<p>We believe that having your own place on the internet should not be limited by how much code you know or how big your budget is. The mission of BlogKub is to <strong>cut the technical barriers of building a site down to the smallest possible.</strong> That way you spend your time on what actually matters, creating good content, rather than fixing code. We keep improving the tool and the guides, holding every feature to the same standard: easy to use, well built, and genuinely useful.</p>

<h2 id="author">The founder of BlogKub</h2>
<div class="card" style="display:flex;gap:20px;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap">
  <img src="/author-patpisan.png" width="96" height="96" loading="lazy" alt="Patpisan Dathong (Ben), founder of BlogKub" style="width:96px;height:96px;border-radius:50%;flex:none;border:2px solid var(--brand)">
  <div style="flex:1;min-width:240px">
    <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:20px">Patpisan Dathong <span style="color:var(--ink-3);font-weight:500;font-size:16px">(Ben, PATPISAN DATHONG)</span></div>
    <p style="margin:.55em 0 .9em;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.75">I am Ben. I have built websites and blogged on Blogger for many years. I created BlogKub because I believe everyone should be able to have a beautiful blog that does real SEO, without writing code or paying a developer. Every guide and article on this site is written from my own hands-on experience building themes, customizing them, and doing SEO on Blogger.</p>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:14px">
      <a href="https://www.facebook.com/patpisan" rel="me noopener" target="_blank" style="padding:6px 14px;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:999px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--brand-2);font-weight:600">Facebook</a>
      <a href="https://pantip.com/profile/2448725" rel="me noopener" target="_blank" style="padding:6px 14px;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:999px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--brand-2);font-weight:600">Pantip (LuMoo)</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<p style="margin-top:26px"><a href="/builder" class="cta">Start using the free tool →</a></p>
</article></main>`;
---
<EnLayout seo={seo} thHref="/about">
  <Fragment set:html={body} />
</EnLayout>
